reviewText: I have always enjoyed these movies. How convenient to get them all on Blu-ray. Great movies, great price, and super convenient. 4 discs, one case.

I was at Wal-Mart today getting some items I needed. I generally swing buy the electronics section to see if there is anything I wouldn't mind getting for my film collection.  Sure enough, there was!  I saw the Final Destination Blu-Ray Collection for $12.96. I already had the 5th on Blu-Ray.  So I said let me get it.
  To my pleasent suprise, they were the special editions of all for films.  I was VERY happy about that!
  Pros: 1) 4 of the 5 Final Destinations in one pack.  2) All of them the special editions with all the extras.  3) Low price (I was suprised that it even beat out Amazon.).
  Cons: 1) It doesn't have all 5.  2) No Ultra-Violet/Digital Copy
  Regardless, I am very happy that I picked thisup

For the price, this is an easy recommendation. You get the first four films in the Final Destination series on four Blu Rays with all the extras intact. Each side of the case takes two discs stacked one on top of the other. Picture and sound is great across the board and again, the price point makes this a must buy for fans of the series. Only thing that would have made this better would have been the inclusion of the fifth film but for what you get, you really can't complain.

Since Amazon didn't include detailed specs for each movie in this set, Im including it here.

All four films are 1080p. 1&2 are 1:85:1 aspect ratio. 3&4 are both 2:4:1.

1, 2 & 3 are all Dolby TruHD 5.1.  4 is DTS-HD master audio 5.1.

All four films include the loads of extras that were on the original DVDscommentaries, making of featurettes, deleted scenes, etc.

Two things seem to be missing from the Blu-ray versions of part 3 & 4:

Part 3 had a sort of choose their fate option when watching the movie, in which you were apparently prompted to answer questions that would change the story. That is not an option in this version of the film. But it appears to have a whole load more extras than the DVD.

The Final Destination (part 4) does not include both the 2D and 3d versions of the film with the red and blue glasses. It is ONLY the 2D version.
